<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-47-0706 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author explains how he uncovered secret talks between the U.S. andCanada for weapons testing in Canada. The story was run in several papers.In Canada several protestors voiced disagreement with the External AffairsMinister on several issues, including the proposed cruise missile testing.Otherwise, there was very little public awareness of the secret negotiations.The author points out that it is difficult to find out about these typesof negotiations because the governments release very little informationand phone calls between the two countries are routinely intercepted,making it difficult for Canadian reporters to talk to sources on thetelephone.</TEXT></DOC>